  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0b8e\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0b9a\u0b95\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf \u0b85\u0bae\u0bc8\u0b9a\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0bae\u0bc1\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0bb5\u0bc8\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4 \u0b8e\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0baa\u0bca\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0bb5\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bc8\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0b9a\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bbe\u0ba9\u0bb5\u0bc8 \u0b85\u0bb2\u0bcd\u0bb2 - \u0ba8\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0bb5\u0bcb\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0b89\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0bae\u0bc8\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bbe\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1 \u0ba4\u0bc7\u0b9a\u0bbf\u0baf \u0b87\u0baf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bae\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Energy Minister's proposed fuel prices are not correct - National Movement for Protection of Consumer Rights",
      "author": "T Yuwaraj",
      "body_lines": [
        "According to the data submitted to the COPE committee, the fuel prices presented recently by the Minister of Power and Energy are not correct.",
        "The National Movement for Protection of Consumer Rights said that the current fuel price presented by the minister is 200 rupees higher than the actual price.",
        "In this regard, Ranjith Vithanage, President of the National Movement for Protection of Consumer Rights, has revealed in a statement,",
        "According to the data released now, all types of fuel can be sold below Rs 300 subject to government tax.",
        "But now all other fuels except kerosene are selling at more than 470 rupees.",
        "Accordingly, it is seen that government and private companies are making more than 200 rupees profit from petrol and diesel.",
        "In this case, there is a risk of increasing the electricity bill due to high cost fuel being supplied to the power generators of the Sri Lanka Electricity Board. In that case the people of the country will have to bear this burden.",
        "There is a huge discrepancy between the data presented by the Energy Minister and the Customs Department regarding fuel prices. But the Chief Accountant Committee of the Government has failed to inspect the accounts in this regard.",
        "The Sri Lankan Petroleum Corporation is said to be implementing prices based on Singapore prices. The Public Utilities Commission said that the prices should be determined according to the price of fuel in the country where the fuel is actually purchased.",
        "Although it is seen that all types of fuel can be reduced by Rs 200, the Consumer Authority is also silent on this.",
        "The government should be held directly responsible if such companies are allowed to steal the money of customers who stand in line for four or five days to get fuel.",
        "Although many years have passed since we raised our voice that we need an independent body to regulate fuel, even today no independent body has been appointed to regulate fuel.",
        "He said he requested the government to take steps to regulate fuel prices and provide real price information to people."
      ],
